{{citations|date=February 2012}} {{use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Axel Axgil | image = Axel and Eigil Axgil.jpg | alt = | caption = Eigil and Axel Axgil in 1950 | birth_name = Axel Lundahl-Madsen | birth_date = 3 April 1915 | birth_place = | death_date = {{death date and age|df=y|2011|10|29|1915|4|3}} | death_place = | resting_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | education = }} {{Infobox person | name = Eigil Axgil | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Eigil Eskildsen | birth_date = 24 April 1922 | birth_place = | death_date = {{death date and age|1995|9|22|1922|4|24|df=y}} September 22, 1995 | death_place = | resting_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | education = }}
'''Axel Axgil''' (3 April 1915 – 29 October 2011) and '''Eigil Axgil''' (24 April 1922 – 22 September 1995) were Danish gay activists and a longtime couple. They were the first [[gay]] couple to enter into a [[Civil union|registered partnership]] anywhere in the world following [[Denmark]]'s legalisation of same-sex partnership registration in 1989, a landmark legislation which they were instrumental in bringing about. They adopted the shared surname, Axgil, a combination of their given names, as an expression of their commitment.
==Biography==
Axel, born '''Axel Lundahl-Madsen''', and Eigil, born '''Eigil Eskildsen''', inspired by the [[Universal Declaration of Human Rights|1948 UN Declaration of Human Rights]], together with several friends, founded ''F-48'' or ''Forbundet af 1948 (The Association of 1948)'', Denmark's first [[gay rights]] organization. By 1951, F-48's membership had grown to 1,339 and there were branches in [[Sweden]] and [[Norway]]. In 1985, F-48 became the [[Danish National Association of Gays and Lesbians]] (''Landsforeningen for Bøsser og Lesbiske, Forbundet af 1948'' or ''LBL''). The couple launched a magazine, ''[[Vennen]] (The Friend)''.
In 1989, Denmark became the first nation in the world to recognize registered partnerships for same-sex couples, nearly equal to (opposite-sex) marriage. On 1 October 1989 the Axgils and 10 other Danish couples were married by Tom Ahlberg, the deputy mayor of [[Copenhagen]], in the [[Copenhagen City Hall|city hall]], accompanied by worldwide media attention. The Axgils had been a couple for 40 years. In 2013, Axel Axgil was named by [[Equality Forum]] as one of their 31 Icons of the [[LGBT History Month]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.equalityforum.com/lgbt-history-month-2013-icons-announced |title=LGBT History Month 2013 Icons Announced – Equality Forum |work=equalityforum.com |accessdate=7 November 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113163342/http://www.equalityforum.com/lgbt-history-month-2013-icons-announced |archivedate=13 January 2016 }}</ref>
==Deaths== Eigil Axgil died on 22 September 1995 at the age of 73.{{cn|date=April 2017}}
Axel Axgil died on 29 October 2011 at the age of 96.{{cn|date=April 2017}}
